==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: dissociated
<hw>dissociated</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>not connected or
associated.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> unconnected.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>diffusing independently in a
fluid; -- said of ions or molecules which may form relatively stable
associated structures; <as>as, the products become rapidly
<ex>dissociated</ex> from the active site of the enzyme</as>. Opposite
of <ant>associated</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dissociation</ent>⟦br⟧
